{"text": "Looking for an emotional rollercoaster and do not want to read lots of text? Then   – it masterfully presents its message through just pictures and music while touching your very soul with its wordless beauty. If anybody ever tells you that games are not work of art, show them this title.  To begin with, I cannot but complement the developers that created this little gem. It is just SO beautiful in every aspect! The artwork is magnificent, and it was obvious just from the screenshots. In the game itself, all pictures look even better. I love this kind of art style – with lots of neat details, calm colors and a bit fairy-tale-like.  Music is also enchanting, and all UI features have their own violin sounds. As I have already mentioned above, there is one tune that is the main connecting point for all parts of the story, and trust me, it will touch your heart the very moment you hear it. What else…ah, right! The point-and-click parts. It is definitely not a hidden-objects game, even though yes, you will need to search for some items. And yes, you do have an inventory. But still, there are no outlines of the objects that you need to find, nor any words that tell you what you need. So, compared to classical examples of the genre – such as many games by bigfish or Artifex Mundi, - I would say that Then When The Past Was Around is definitely a point-and-click title. This part aside, there are enough interactive features to keep you entertained through the whole story. Speaking of the puzzles, all of them are really interesting, even though several still confused me. My main advice here is to look for clues. Some are well-hidden and require major brain work, while others are in the open sight or will come in later. So try to be as be attentive as possible, it is worth it. Oh, by the way, as a good example of why rushing through this game is a bad idea, let me tell you the epic tale of my grandiose stupidity. There was a puzzle with numbers that you need to find somewhere. I immediately noticed several leads and started cracking them. Combination after combination, I began doubting both myself and the game: is it broken? Is there some kind of glitch? Why is not it working?! An hour later, I gave up and brought my mother into the fight. We both searched for clues, tried mixing numbers and just everything possible, but once again nothing worked. ‘OK’, I said and started bugging two of my close friends. They also decided to join my epic battle with the puzzle and offered their own suggestions.  An hour and a half have passed…I was almost ready to just close the game and leave it before I decided to throw my laptop out of the window. And then, finally, it hit me! The solution was in front of me the whole damn time – and I just decided to overlook it. It was so simple, and yet I spent 90 minutes chasing an absolutely different thing. Well, my friends and mum definitely had a good laugh at my expense when I told them what I was doing wrong. And so did I, to be honest, because my mistake was hilarious. So, boys, girls and young individuals, do not repeat my mistake!  In the end, the only thing I can say is do not think twice: buy this masterpiece right away. And then spend a bit more money and purchase the artbook and the soundtrack too.   is worth every coin and minute you spend on it, and its touching story will leave you craving for more. The best part is that it is both inspiring and mysterious until the very end - it leaves some unanswered questions, but does not feel unfinished; instead, this game lets your imagination run free. And it is amazing.", "appid": "1164050", "steamid": "profiles/76561198032544384", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "63", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600776000.0}
{"text": "Да, это длс, выпущенное как полноценная игра. Да, вышла в одно время с единством, но с графикой как АС3 Да, ассасинов и тамплиеров просто поменяли местами. Несмотря на всё это я не жалею что потратил на изгоя 30 часов. Как никак приятно увидеть до боли знакомых персонажей и увидеть такой поворот в финале. никаких геймплейных инноваций как и визуальных, но всё это знакомо, словно, родное. Это последний проект, который остался на одной ступени, ведь после него Юбики начали подниматься выше, оставив многие детали здесь. и да для меня АС умерла с началом Истоков, про одиссею вообще молчу....", "appid": "311560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198364819184", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1576238400.0}
