{"text": "Spectacular game - great music, characters, storyline, an ongoing sidequest/hunt/mission for a dancing mask man who'll teach you how to move stylishly - it has it all. The game is stellar with it's artstyle and it's colours and the puzzles have the perfect difficulty to make the game a nice relaxing experience. The controls are simple, but some movement can be a little janky in rare instances (wind puzzle, looking at you here). It all culminates in a lovely ending, with a pleasant and pleasing message running through it and blooming at the end with a lovely \"Thanks for playing <3\".  I got the game as a part of Humblebundle Monthly, and then got all of the achievements because I enjoyed it so much. £15 might look a little steep, but if you love puzzle games, or a game you can play to relax then grab this gem. If you're unsure, maybe wait for a sale, but there's an easy 10 hours of content here if you play at a nice pace.", "appid": "530320", "steamid": "profiles/76561197989509447", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1566388800.0}
