{"text": "Everybody who gave this DLC a bad review is living proof that psychological understanding (and treatment) is utter s**t in 99% of the world. As a person who suffers from mental illness this is the hardest a game or even a DLC has ever hit. Yes it is outlandish and overly violent but the symbolism and the core functions of mental illness and coming to terms with said mental illness and even reaching out for help when things are at the worst are all there. There are even philosophy references, including \"Plato's Cave\" (look it up). If you suffer from any type of mental illness, please, play this DLC and take your time playing it.", "appid": "1233061", "steamid": "profiles/76561198077502734", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599912000.0}
