{"text": "Lust for darkness is a game that caught my attention because they told me that we would unravel a case about the disappearance of our wife and I love mystery stories  (͡ ° ͜ʖ ͡ °). . This is a game recommended for people over 18 years as it has various sexual content and obscene language so if you are under 18 this may not be the right game for you. As well as said in this game we assume the role of a man whose wife has been missing for a lot of days, and suddenly receives a letter at home to go to a mansion try to rescue her.  From then on we are joining all the pieces of the puzzle trying not to be caught by the men of the board. This is a game with a story and graphics similar to the game agony. The gameplay mode is a bit bad, I think they should change the mechanics of the game of opening and closing doors because we are always a bit clumsy to try to open the doors, in terms of graphics I think it could also improve a bit since the game is recent. The lack of ability to use weapons in the game reminds me when I played Outlast, but in this case the developer could have put a revolver or a knife because the story becomes a little drying up to have to always run away from our enemies. The story and the idea of ​​the game are good as well as its soundtrack but this title does not seem to be one of the best sequels of terror, In my case I spent the game in one day so I found the game very short. In spite of this, I offer my sincere congratulations to you who thought of building the most piquant scenes (͡ ° ͜ʖ ͡ °). If you like fap games  (͡ ° ͜ʖ ͡ °), and mystery this is a game for you. Final note: 7-10", "appid": "523650", "steamid": "profiles/76561198178875206", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "20", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530446400.0}
