{"text": "It's a shame when devs go under before polishing a good idea. The game gets a bad rap, and that's sad considering the lack of DMC clones out there. It's a shame this genre is so limited to only a few hyped and polished entries. The game HAS been aquired by the publisher !C company and both those who stave for, and like this game, as well as those who bemoan the lack of games in this genre are hoping they will polish it up to a better state. , The combat was quite fun as well once you knew how to properly use your skills and the story was actually pretty good. Way better than down-voters say, I didn't have, or seem to have,m near the tech problems the bombers claim though I do not deny the game company went bye-bye before they could polish it and bug trap it to an acceptable level, though It's still very fun, it WOULD be worth the full price if 1C would slap some polish and squash some bugs where-as now, unfortunately, it remains a \"get on sale\" title. Which they could change quickly as what tech issues are there (to anyone who plays games for awhile) can tell aren't really that hard of a fix. It would only take minimal to moderate work to bring tit to a well loved state., I've had fun with it, and got it in hopes to see it improved by 1C. They hold the hand and I believe with a little interest ahnd support from fans may indeed do some work on it.", "appid": "887720", "steamid": "profiles/76561198032137848", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598616000.0}
