{"text": "My Electric Scribe review:  This game is very similar to Electric Scribe but I don't know which came first so I won't accuse one for copying the other. they are both a lot of fun to play, they just have a few small rather insignificant differences. 1) Pipes! requires you to get 3 stars on all levels in order to unlock all achievements.  Electric Scribe doesn't. However the levels on Pipes! are so much easier compared to Electric Scribe, that it evens out and you get 3 stars on all levels rather easily. 2) Electric Scribe features different sized puzzles, some are really large, requiring you to scroll up and down and sideways to see the whole puzzle.  Pipes! uses the same exact sized puzzle throughout its 90 puzzles with different patterns to solve inside. and lastly  3) Electric Scribe and Pipes! both have the same mechanic of rotating the pieces so they fit together. Pipes! feautres a second mechanic of sliding certain pieces up/down left/right to help solve the puzzle, HOWEVER this mechanic only came into play in ONE out of 90 puzzels. So I didn't really understand why it existed in the first place. I recommend both games, if you're going to play both start with Pipes! first and then advance to Electric Scribe. have fun! :)", "appid": "755890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198060237017", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1518868800.0}
