{"text": "I kinda feel like I was raped.. but in a good way. I bought the game because it said it was multi player and I had a friend that was also going to buy it so we could play but after both of us sitting there for 20 minutes stoned trying to figure out how to make Multi player work, we came to realize it was false advertising and there was no online or offline multi player. Their concept of multi player is racing your friends ghosts, which is pretty weak. With that being said this game is ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ Amazing. Smoke a joint, pound a beer, or go balls out and drop a couple tabs of acid and ride the Riff. It's like Audio Surf and 90's retro racer had a baby. Now its more of a racer then it is audio surf in the sense your not dodging blocks while picking up others that are all placed to the beat, Riff Racer's enviroment is effected by the beat, Big jumps/ drops in the track are usually timed with bass drops or heavy bass. The visuals are also effected by the tempo of the song. Overal the game is well done, graphics are great for the vibe of the game, the controls with a controler are fluent and flowing, making drifting fun and engaging, and a level system and multiple vihicles and paint upgrades adds a want to play more. best way to out it, over the past 3 days while working 8 hours each day, walking the dog and hour each day and playing beer league 2 of those days 2 hours each i have managed to put on 8 hours of play time and when im not playing it, it has my skin itching. 10/10", "appid": "351990", "steamid": "profiles/76561198007874403", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1467288000.0}
