{"text": "is a short kinetic visual novel with family and slice-of-life content developed by  , a well-known author in the VN community for making other great titles such as  ,  , and  . She is one of my favorite western authors in the VN community as well, and I really like the way she describes her characters' point of view and feelings. Her approach to more heartwarming themes such as family and friendship is also a nice change of pace if you're used to reading more adult themed novels like myself.   In this visual novel, we follow the story of Yuu, a young man who just got back from Tokyo to spend the holiday season with his relatives in their small town. After spending some time with his parents and his (not so nice) younger sister, he decides to visit his grandmother, Umeko. Everything seems fine at first until they both make a wish after seeing a shooting star across the sky during that night. On the next day, Umeko simply became cute and young again! Now, they both have to find out what happened and how can Umeko turn back to her normal self. The plot sounds like something that came straight from a comedy movie, to be honest. I was a bit skeptical about it, but it turns out that...     is a story about the passage of time, of getting older and missing people that now are gone. But it's also a story of love, family, and it makes you think:  Let's talk about the appearance of this title. The sprites are cute, and so are the CGs.   The BGM is mostly good, but a few songs are kind of too loud in certain scenes. The UI is simple and cute, and I like it! Overall, it's a visually pleasing game that comes with a fair price. There's also the author's notes which you can read after finishing the game. I finished this novel in two hours, reading at a fast pace.  7.5/10. I highly recommend   if you want a cute and short novel that will make you smile and, maybe, even shed a tear.", "appid": "925340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198120348301", "voted_up": true, "votes_up":