{"text": "Stellaris is the best space sandbox i have ever played. I started playing this game when it first came out in 2016, the stellaris you see now is not even close to what it was when it first came out. Stellaris have gone through a couple of middle age crises and i would say that each major big update have made the game better.  Sure the game have some issue. If you understand what to do you can easily snowball the game and remove all the challenges, but biggest issue is that when you hit somewhere between middle and late game the game full run about as fast as a snail, i have a old low tier pc and let me tell you 1 day in the game in late game takes about 5 to 10 seconds to happen and i can literally go to the store for about 1 hour before even a year have past in the late game. I have about 200 hours without mods and the rest is with mods and mods can change the game so much, i cant even play vanilla anymore, the reason why i come back every now and then is because i find some new bizarre mod that looks fun to try. There are a lot of dlc for the game, play the base game before buying dlcs and if you enjoy the game but don't want to buy all the dlcs i would recommend \"Utopia\" Synthetic Dawn Story Pack\" and \"MegaCorp\"", "appid": "281990", "steamid": "profiles/76561198035713281", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "63", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603454400.0}
