{"text": "I'm having tons of fun playing this with my girlfriend. Planning our actions beforehand and tactically executing them is awesome. (Such as counting to three and shooting two enemies talking to each other simultaneously.) We particularly enjoy playing the classic sniper/spotter duo. It's like playing the MGS V story mode online.  The game is truly immersive and beautiful with highly customizable graphics options. Runs alright at medium settings even on my girlfriend's older (GTX 850M) hardware. There are many different landscapes and areas to visit. A big plus in my book. What I like the most is you can do whatever you want in this game at any given time. I love it when an open world game gives me freedom. Well, I like dressing up my characters in games. Especially in a military setting. >Wear a ghillie suit and go prone in a bush in the middle of a jungle. >Shoot at a random enemy from 600 meters away with a suppressed sniper rifle. >His body is found a few minutes later. >20 enemies running straight to you aiming at your face. >3 SUVs spawned right behind you and an attack helicopter is circling above you.  >Enemy spots you aiming at him with an AR for a moment and screams with panic. >Quickly take cover before the detection bar fills up. >Enemy sits down, pops open a beer and starts reading comics. Too arcadey controls combined with the super weird physics engine of the game is really off-putting. I don't know if I dislike it because I've invested too much time into various air combat simulators back in the day but no rudder control in a 2017 game is unacceptable. Did something go wrong while doing a stealth playthrough? Time to go back to main menu or kill yourself with a grenade. Annoying. Did you have fun spraying the water with your chopper's chain gun just to see the splash effects and admire the graphics of the game? Good. You've just ruined your accuracy and stealth stats permanently. Even if you delete your save files, you're out of luck. No way to start this game from scratch. No, you can't farm the in-game currency by any means. You need to pay real money to get cosmetic items and it's a randomized process. I can't stand crates. Need I say more? You have to give your money to them in order to play this.", "appid": "460930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198016513479", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1523966400.0}
