{"text": "It's another day in your neighborhood, walking down the street and admiring the people around you, angry and bored because it's another day to do errands, you spent the last five minutes kicking a can around since it is better to be distracted with something rather than your small piece of paper. You come across an alleyway which leads to the grocery store, while walking through filth and rubble, you discover a shovel amongst some old boxes and, with care, you pick it up and admire its looks and glory, an idea appeared with the smile on your face. Later that day, you come home with your clothes and shovel tainted red, sit on the couch and rest, happy since you got to finish those stupid errands... with extreme prejudice! Throughout the week, Postal dude is forced to do errands by his annoying wife, having no other easy solution to the situation, survival and patience are a requirement to face the opressing groups of protestors, the people who fired him days after hiring him, the mascot Krotchy who's got skeletons in his closet, law enforcement units, taliban terrorists, a religious cult, butchers and Gary Coleman. All this with his four legged buddy Champ and a box of blue tip Arizona matches. The keyboard controls in this game have a perfect timing while the mouse is the opposite, but that can be changed in the option menu, as well it features a console controller inputs in case the keyboard is not for you. Worth mentioning that the game has got an advanced option menu to make it run smoothly, I found it really helpful with my gameplay. It's an open world game, based on RWS's brutal dark humor, where throughout the week you have to complete chores or ''errands'', as the game implies, either chaotically or peacefully while each part of the map is unlocked after completing the said day of the week ready to explore and with 15 difficulties to choose from, ranging from ''Liebermode'', the easiest, and ''Impossible'', the hardest, the game only changes a lot of features when you play above the ''Postal'' difficulty, for example, health itens cannot be stored in the inventory and the amount of bullets you can carry gets shortened, while the last example is affected by every difficulty... There are numerous of features and mechanics included, the AI may not be the best one but sure executes the job right, animals are one of those features, for example, there are dogs who can be useful, if you have dog treats or food, to take down foes while cats, in Zack Ward's style and if you have catnip, are common to be used as both shotgun and M16 silencers. Not to forget to mention,it includes a mechanic detector where it can help you if you are stuck on some corner of the map and weapon spawns changes depending on the day of the week, sometimes you can get more or something different from what you wanted. Since this game is a Steam version, where it includes ''Share The Pain'', ''Apocalypse Weekend'', ''A Week in Paradise'' and as well a online mode, it supports Steam's Workshop, which until this day is still used by some people. The design of the map is small with mysterious places and with a creepy atmosphere but sure leaves a certain impression of realism with its inhabitants, without them, it wouldn't be the same... Achievements? Well, the brutal dark humor from RWS found itself present on the achievements and boy oh boy! What a bunch... Most of them are completely easy, some require items to complete like food or the outfits you can wear but the most difficult one I could do was the ''Anustart!'', complete the main 5 days without killing anyone, with so many weapons and so many victims, it truly was hard for me not to kill anyone! ''Scientology Level: OT VIII'', complete an entire on ''Postal'' difficulty, to be honest, it may be hard at first but when you get the right weapons, it just becomes easier. You occasionally may find some bodies and limbs cliping through walls and such or the game crashes when you die too many times or there is too many NPCs for the game to process but that can be fixed in the option menu. Chaotically fascinating and hilarious spending time listenning to Postal Dude's voice lines, I had so much fun playing it and completing everything, while the NPC's made the gameplay more interesting with their shenanigans and the ''Postal'' difficulty was one of the purest experiments to play because it represents the insanity of the game itself, truly would recomend it to somebody who isn't sensitive towards RWS's humor or wants to have the best time of their life, in other words, I regret nothing! Score: 9,5/10", "appid": "223470", "steamid": "profiles/76561198823468150", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "60", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1570190400.0}
{"text": "王女（姫）にラブレターを渡す事をモチーフとしたカードゲーム。 配られる手札は2枚で、順番に1枚づつ場にオープンして相手のカードを攻撃。カードの優劣で相手を蹴落として最後まで生き残るか、最終得点が多い人が勝利する。 カードの左上に数字があり、これが攻撃力となる。同じく左側面に記された星はそのカードがゲーム中に存在する数で、オープンされる毎に星が塗りつぶされていく。（これでどのカードが残っているか予測する事が出来る） 全8種類という少ない種類のカードで優劣を競い合う。 各カードの特性から相手のカードを予測するという、単純だが気軽にハマるには奥が深いシステムが面白い。 衛兵・王子カードの存在はゲームを速攻終わらせる可能性があるが、それでなくても手持ちの札が2枚で1ゲームはすぐに終了する為、カジュアルに息抜きが出来るゲームだ。", "appid": "926520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198313189000", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575892800.0}
