{"text": "Vampyr is certainly a unique game! The combat is fun and challenging and (It's almost a cliche to say this at this point but it's true!) it is really similar to the \"Dark Souls\" series style of combat, though not as in depth as those games. The world and atmosphere are top notch, even if I found them to be a bit too depressing and creepy at times, which is probably what the developers were going for so... good job Dontnod I guess! The story and the characters are definitely the highlight of the game, with a dialogue system that is pretty meaty and a morality system that affects how the story plays out depending on your actions and what kind of vampire you want Jonathan Reid to be. All in all Vampyr is a great memorable experience with plenty of personality and charm that's worth your time if you appreciate RPGs with a good story.", "appid": "427290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198129921987", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529668800.0}
