{"text": "This is a no brainer for a dollar (60% off when I got it). 95% of the songs are catchy as hell.  It's an excellent introduction to rhythm games and everyone can get behind the gameplay as long you don't hate animu artstyle. Definitely a fun game to play to relax. I only know 1 song from the game and still absolutely love pretty much all the music choices. I'll definitely consider buying the DLC if you like the base game. While I would consider this casual, harder maps can get cluttered and my eyes just hurt after 45 minutes because of the bright art style and the horizontal scrolling wouldn't let my eyes fixed on 1 position of the screen. You can't change the horizontal scroll speed of every song so it's tough to sight read the maps on the highest difficulty. This is the main reason why my eyes hurts after a long play session and why I wouldn't go hardcore mode on this game The UI to navigate to a song is bad, you have to know which tab the music resides and have to scroll a lot on the default music tab.", "appid": "774171", "steamid": "profiles/76561198046980920", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592049600.0}
