{"text": "I've played over 2000 hours of this game over a period of about 4-5 years. First discovered it by watching my dad play - i soon took over the computer and he wasnt playing ck2 anymore. This was just after i graduated from 8th grade. With mountain dew i stayd up for almost 4 days mostly playing ck. I pirate ck2 on my laptop and play so im not ALWAYS hogging the desktop and so i could play when away fom his house. (before india is relased), Then I get the real game around charlemange time.   Freshman  year of high school, world history.  Teacher talks about islam and the byzantines, i already know everything from CK2, he thinks im a genius but in reality i just no lifed a video game all summer. Dlc are released inbetween, game gets better. 2018, Senior year of highschool, Holy Fury DLC is released, possibly the last one. Tons of new features, warrior lodges, way better way to reform pagan religions, you really can shape it into what you want it to be, a religion of war, peace, or learning and scholarship. This is the best strategy game I have ever played, it goes beyond just warfare into the intrigue and diplomacy of the world and your realm.. Def worth a buy. The thing is though, what many people dislike is the DLC policy. The game was released in 2012, is 2018, Each year a couple of DLC's are released providing massive updates, new features (some free) and general better things to the game. Well all of the dlc's released over the years add up to a lot of money. But i say have 2-3 10$-20$ dlcs released every year is better then a new 60$ game every year that studios like Activision release. So the game is worth a buy, but FOR SURE do it on sale so you can get as many dlc's as possible. Another alternative is to buy the dlc for cheaper on a third party key selling website.", "appid": "203770", "steamid": "profiles/76561198124607397", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1417608000.0}
{"text": "Let me tell you something about this game, ok? I'm a builder, I know how to build things, the best in the industry. The best. Its true, its true. I know a lot of people, I know how to make deals. China beats us all the time. You know China right? They beat us ALL the time. But I love the Chinese, I make great deals with them! That's the point, they have smart leaders, we have stupid leaders. But not anymore, not anymore. So this game shows up and it's like WHAT? Subscription based? Ay ay ay, I knew it wouldn't last long. And guess what I was RIGHT. It went F2P. You know why? Because they realized how stupid they were and they took my advice, make it F2P, create a lot of ingame purchases, and you have to tell the Chinese, “Listen you motherf—–s! We’re going to tax you 25 percent!” and it will work! So this game goes F2P, and guess what the ratings go up,  they make better expansions, but then a new guy takes over and screws everything up. This total loser Perfect World Entertainment. who by the way is so low in the polls he should just drop out. Can you believe it? He spent so much money on ads and he's at 3% I spent almost NOTHING and I'm on top. Anyways, it doesn't matter, it doesn't matter. I keep seeing these new ships in the game from the Delta Quadrant. Who wants to play in the Delta Quadrant? And now they are bringing them in can you believe it? They’re bringing drugs, they’re bringing crime, they’re rapists, they should not be anywhere near our solar system. We will build a wall I tell you, which by the way Mexico will pay for, we will do it. And it's going to be so high once you go up you wont want to come down. Anyways, this game, it's good, it's good, you should play it before our leaders make another stupid deal. Oh and by the way, the media, they are totally dishonest, some of the worst people out there, not all of them, but most. Don't trust the reviews. Look at them they wont move the cameras! They never show the crowd they have the camera zoomed in to my face! HEY you blonde lady! Turn the cameras around, turn them around! I will make America great again, I will do it. It needs to be done. It needs to, we have no choice!", "appid": "9900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198051230899", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "59", "votes_funny": "261", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1453636800.0}
