{"text": "The best KOF after XIII and XI will get playable netcode on October 1st. Now I can recommend one of the best fighting games out there. Edit: Might add KOF14 on the list now that I have lost to everyone 0-100 in this game too. 2002UM is really fun but the controls don't feel as good as in newer games. Most of the difficulty in combos comes from how tight the cancel timings are - to the point it feels clunky rather than fun challenge. The difficult combos in KOF13 feel more fun, even if I can't do them at all. Input buffer is so long that you can accidentally get command normals and special moves. Easiest way to test this is with Angel. Cancel run into db+B by doing a half circle motion (f, df, d, db + B) and Angel will do df+B command normal unless you delay B a lot. Then there are other weird stuff like Quick MAX activation causing you to do B/C normals despite doing the input only once and max mode cancel weirdness. Blue Mary for example, has to be careful inputting [4]~6D -> 236A/C in Max Mode so you don't accidentally do her overhead special move. Also not a big fan of how low reward you often get for spending resources for damage. Doing max mode combos without SDM enders or spending one bar on super feels unrewarding. This is noticeable with close Heavy starters that deal almost as much damage no matter if you use 1 bar super or start it in max mode. You use MAX mode to get more damage from specials, command normals and far range normals but even then the damage can feel unrewarding compared to KOF11, 13 and 14 due to the damage scaling. Still a great game though aside from those issues. Please don't send Nameless/Kasumi/K' players to bully me.", "appid": "222440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198028057411", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601294400.0}
