{"text": "WASTED is a fantastic game that surprisingly feels like a spin-off to Fallout, perhaps a more insane, punishing and comedic spin-offs but considering its made by basically one person its a great accomplishment.  Normally i avoid roguelike games like the plague BUT I've thrown over 25+ hrs into this and the charm and atmosphere keeps brining me back, not to mention the incredible soundtrack and pretty good voice over (for all characters other than the player), there is a plethora of weapons and armor, that can both be modded and some unique type can be crafted from acquired diagrams.  The dungeons or \"Coolers\" are randomly generated aside from the last floor and/or Boss levels. You can earn house upgrades throughout the game and find new hair styles for the NPCs and each of your generated/created characters.   You get some quests with choice/consequence for example not having to fight certain bosses etc.  Overall a great game and I cant wait to see what the future holds for it, be DLC or a sequel.", "appid": "327510", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970675272", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1466078400.0}
