{"text": "If you're like me and are very picky when it comes to platformers, Celeste is one of the top-notch ones. The mechanics are a little more involved, with 8-way dashing and a wall climb button, and for that reason I highly recommend using a keyboard. I tried playing this game with a controller and can't count the number of times I dashed the wrong direction on the analog stick. That out of the way, the controls are very responsive and while it will take some time to get used to the dashing/climbing, when you come back to earlier stages to collect the strawberries you missed, you'll see just how much you've improved at the game overall. A really nice thing Celeste does is teach you new tricks to add to your arsenal, and it does this all throughout the game. Even on the last levels of Celeste's B-side (the equivalent of Super Meat Boy's dark world levels) you're still being introduced to new movement tech you might not have known before. That goes to show how in-depth the mechanics are in this game. Rather than in-game rewards like in Super Meat Boy, the reward for mastery is empowerment. You'll want to collect every strawberry almost as if you're telling the game \"Don't worry bro, I got this\". And for the ones that are too hard at first, you can leave the nest and come back later and show how much you've grown, which is a very satisfying feeling. Those moving platforms and spikes you had trouble with at the start? They're child's play now. Celeste becomes very difficult, yes, but it wants you to succeed, and greatly respects your time and commitment. There are a few things I don't care for like certain hazards *coughpinballbumpers* and enemy cycles later on that you have to negotiate while plummeting to your death, but overall, Celeste deserves to stand in the hall of platforming giants like Super Meat Boy.", "appid": "504230", "steamid": "profiles/76561198018056824", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "28", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1533470400.0}
{"text": "Firstly, I don't really enjoy first person shooters at all. But this game is so different from those! I'm so glad I decided to give it a go. With not much experience in FPS games I was struggling with the fights sometimes, there wasn't much variety in gameplay, but I didn't care, because the fantastic sceneries and the atmosphere totally got me. You start playing and you just step into another world! The graphics, the style, the story... this game is pure art. <3 This is definitely one of the best games I've played. My jaw dropped not once, and not only twice... Now after the ending I have to go look for it again, wish me luck. :)", "appid": "8870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198029156645", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1381320000.0}
