{"text": "Counter-Strike: Global Offensive is a multiplayer first-person shooter video game developed by Valve and Hidden Path Entertainment. It is the fourth game in the Counter-Strike series and was released for Windows, OS X, Xbox 360, and PlayStation 3 in August 2012, while the Linux version was released in 2014 and I want to tell that the day I first tried CSGO at a PC cafe, I fell in love. It's why I own a PC from MSI of my own today, and why gaming and FPS titles in general became a major part of my life. Counter-Strike has one of the largest fanbased communities backing it up, which quickly becomes apparent with a quick YouTube or Twitch search. I think that everything include video games has its pross and its cons so the supporting argument why you should to play CS: GO is that CS: GO features new maps, characters, weapons, and game modes, and delivers updated versions of the classic CS. CS: GO also has the upper hand in terms of combat mechanics. Weapons and movement especially feel more accurate than in TF2, Fortnite and PUBG. All these factors make for a much more condensed and manageable experience. I particularly enjoy that matches tend to only take about 10 minutes from start to finish. CS: GO stands as a glowing reminder that quality game design is rewarded in longevity and variety. Though it has its disadvantages too. For instance the toxicity level in this game is amazingly high. Also CS: GO is nice game and gameplay, but full of cheaters...you shouldn't make this game free..now u must improve your anticheat. If you're only now getting into PC gaming, the first thing you need to do is buy yourself a copy of CSGO, whether you're a fan or not. It's just an unspoken rule. OK, so note that it is the best free to play fps shooting game! I'm grateful for every single person who's played a hand in this legendary title's development, and I know it'll be quite some time before I lose interest in what it offers. You've got the training course, vs. AI, community deathmatch, and ranked matches once you get more serious. The players have created countless surf maps, too, so you'll always have something new to master. To sum up I personally recommend everyone to plz plz play this game. It's too awesome, better than any other PC game. The day I played this game, I literally got so much addicted that I cannot Express myself now. So good luck and have fun everyone :)", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198072735411", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0}
