{"text": "In Dragon Rage our goal is to destroy the whole village and its residents, which can be reached after slaying the king. We can kill in several ways: to burn with flames from our mouth, to trample, to crush by dashing, to consume which regenerates life and allows you to achieve a state of fury called \"RAMPAGE!!\". This boost makes our beast extreemly powerful for a short time. The trick is to keep our combo (a wave of destrucion) - we should constantly attack and devout humans to go with the flow as well as to increase the point multiplier, because this way leads to beat the highest final score. This game reminds me a series of Rampage and Godzilla franchise. The difference is that the game developed by one dev studio Bulletproof Outlaws is faster, more chaotic and very short, basically like a demo or a game in the early access but it doesn't look like the final version. Last but not least, Dragon Rage is too easy - I finished it at the first attempt without knowledge about the mechanics, tactics and so on and so for. I played around 10 minutes to do it. Well, one way or another, I like the design, music, sound, gameplay and I think that it's quite cool production, but in my opinion it's not worth 7 euros as long as (a lot of!) additional content will be created and implemented, which has already been promised by developer. If you want to support the game creator, you can buy it right now, otherwise you should wait for the price reduction. By the way, Dragon Rage is (also) a title of game developed and published by 3DO on PlayStation 2, so I think that Bulletproof Outlaws should change the name of its production. Thanks for reading my short review.", "appid": "498190", "steamid": "profiles/76561198033142997", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1470139200.0}
