{"text": "Hero-U: Rogue to Redemption Hero-U: Rogue to Redemption is a point & click adventure with RPG elements. The beginning scene is spoilerfree fast told: You are Shawn O'Connor and trying to steal a special coin in a contract of someone. You end up in a university where you are trying to become a rogue legend. You meet interesting and unusual classmates, trying to increase friendship with them and training your skills. In the manner of classic adventures like Quest for Glory (QfG), the \"Hero-U\" dev team pogrammed the QfG btw, you generate your character by answering 10 questions and distributing points to skills and attributes like luck, agility, stealth, gambling, combat etc. But you can increase them later by either training special lessons or using them in real situations. What i liked was the atmosphere of the game, it's a charming, funny game with addictive elements of trying to find out what will happen next. I am on day 8 and still didn't checked all places and was not outside of university. The music background is good and not annoying. From technical view i had some strange behavior elements: intro movie was stuttering in intervals and the walk/run animation of Shawn was weird. I think it's maybe the problem with physics, if you have 144 Hertz monitor you will see it. To solve it: simply limit the frames (fps) to 60-90 fps with either nvidia inspector or other pogramms. This game contains a lot of reading, searching and backtracking. A map or shortcuts would really save a lot of time.  . You collect gold but you need to train your skills by doing lessons or learning on your own. As you do something the time progresses and the day advances. Some quests are open at specific times. People on forum talk about time limit but i didn't see anything till now, day 8. Overall a good designed adventure with RPG elements, unfortunately the days are too short :-) This rating system is my personal opinion and not to be intended to replace a professional rating system in any way! Rating (% out of 100% * X out of 10, sum of all as final rating X/10) My personal rating is  A wanna be master thief caught between the questions of either be a gentleman and good hearted rogue or an evil burglar. Shawn O'Conner in the role of his life, on the way to the top as rogue legend, flirting with beautiful women, meeting mysterious strangers and peting evil cats. Charming adventure with RPG elements in the style of Quest for Glory games. If you liked the review you can follow us as curator: and/or join our group:", "appid": "375440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198125567580", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1531396800.0}
