{"text": "Overkill's The Walking Dead is a different kind of game than any other zombie shooters out there, and it turned into a big controversy for Overkill, but It sure doesn't deserve all the hates.  This review is gonna be a long long review but if you're curious that this game is worth a buy or not, I would say  \"Yes\" If you're a walking dead fan that want to experience some hardship the characters in the show have on scavenging hunts or fight with other survivors.  \"No\"  If you want a mindless zombie shooting game or a game that makes you feel like an ultimate zombie killer. -The Prices- Yeah..... it's kinda expensive and it's gonna be a big factor for most people, This price will cover 2 seasons of the game though.. if that helps haha. The game consists of 2 game modes mainly. Defensive missions and Expedition missions.  -The first ones you'll have to defend against walkers or other hostiles, You'll have to deploy traps, craft medical supplies,  make grenades. barricade the doors in order to survive the hordes. Co-operation is the key to get through the missions. In normal mode, you might not notice much of how hard these missions can be, but in the higher difficulty you play, you'll have to understand the noise mechanic and walkers behavior very well in order to survive. And yes... The supplies and bullets are still limited, You and your teammates need to prioritize the resources while defending your base. Some selfish acts from 1 person in a crucial moment could fail your mission. -The second ones are missions that you need to go out there searching for things, This is where the game shines the most. The resources are all limited. Walkers are all around you, making noise will attract those around and the more noise you make will bring the heat level up... after that point walkers that are not in the area will come to you. You'll have to face the walkers, humans with the very limited supplies and bullets. All the decisions will show up in front of your face... How many bullets can you shoot before the suppressors broke? Which ones should be killed first? by what method? Should you spend your tool to open a shortcut? or should you save it for loots? Should you go through all the walkers and flying bullets to help your friend at the cost of mission or just let him/her die? and many more..... You'll have good time with your friends that is for sure, and you might find good friends playing the game with strangers, Some of them even provide you with great knowledge on how to play the game effectively. With this long long review, It should imply clearly that I really love this game, However it's not a perfect game sadly. The bugs are there, The match making system is still being improved, The cheaters are still ruining the gaming experience.  The good news is that the dev team is very friendly and they're working on all the fixed and updates everyday. With the first episode of a second season coming, they're still fixing the bugs they can in every patch updated. With all that being said 7/10 for now, I hope they'll keep improving it.", "appid": "717690", "steamid": "profiles/76561198063418879", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1543233600.0}
