{"text": "If you are into 4 player coop PvE, this is the best there is. You can play SP or from 2-4 player Coop. The game has difficulty levels (hazard levels) but also scales to the amount of players in the game. If you play SP, you get a helper bot so you are not alone. Additional to that,  there is cave complexity difficulties and overall difficulties. The maps are procedurally generated so every game if different.  Because of the procedurally generated maps, the game download and disk space is amazingly small. When I verify my game files, it takes about 10 seconds. There are 4 classes to play but you are not forced to play 1 of each. If you want, you can play the same class for all 4 players.  To enhance the Coop game type, all gems, XP, and money are shared with all players equally. Even if you didn't make the escape ship. This really promotes team game play more than any game I have played. The game is in EA right now but not to worry. The developers are active in the forums, they listen and offer frequent updates fixing stuff and adding content. The game keeps getting better and better. The graphics are great but take on a somewhat Minecraft look. I hesitated buying this game because of that. After a few games you will see that this fits the game perfectly and once you are in the heat of battle, that blocky look isn't noticeable anymore. All aspects of the game just gel and work together. I cannot recommend this game enough. I put 2000 hours into L4D2 and I can see myself exceeding that here.", "appid": "548430", "steamid": "profiles/76561197973316775", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1551873600.0}
