{"text": "My opinion on this game is that in short, I love it but it is not for everyone. For example the physics and aiming can be hard to get a hold of but once you get to a point where you are decent at the game, it is great. Now for my opinion in long. I bought this game about 18 months ago, I played it a little on the world mode on version 25 but that was just a mass kill on sight battle. Then I went away for a while playing other games until version 27 came out, then I played and mastered aiming and other skills then got bored and left again. The next series of updates came out very quickly and transformed the game entirely, now it is so much more fun. Some of my favourite parts about it is that the game does not limit you, it just tells you how to make money, if you want you can pretend to sell burgers at the Isle Of Burgers, you can go kill everyone and take all the money but please don't do that because it is annoying. Although people may not like it, you are able to do it, I have been on servers where two groups of 10 battled it out with grenades, M16, cars, ext. Those fights happen more often than people give credit too.  Pros: Purely physics based, meaning you can do back flips over cars or dive through windows, slide down roofs ext. The aiming can be good and bad, if you put the work in it is great. (I will be making a guide on aiming soon.) Car mechanics work well. Fantastic opportunities. Great types of missions and overall idea. Cons: Community can be toxic sometimes. The map does not have enough items in it (Chairs, tables ext) A little bit buggy. Note: If you have any questions before buying the game you can contact me, just add me on steam and once I accept you just ask me.", "appid": "272230", "steamid": "profiles/76561198191266815", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1505044800.0}
