{"text": "I wasn't having a good time with this one when I first started. I felt weak and I was dying too many times. But after finding a few upgrades and abilities, it balanced out. Then I found a few more and I felt like a freaking god. The most notable part of this game, to me, is the movement. When you dash into a triple jump, grapple an enemy and triple jump again before launching, the gameplay is second to none. The feel is somewhat like Celeste in that regard. The thing I enjoyed the least, however, has to be the races. This should have been a high point for me, for their usage of the moveset, but each one had too tight of a time limit and took a few too many tries to win. Thankfully, they are all doable as long as you don't mind bashing your head against the wall a little bit. Also, they are completely optional if you're just looking to finish the game. If you know your PC won't have trouble running this, this game is a no brainer for metroidvania fans.", "appid": "1057090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198128385623", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584619200.0}
