{"text": "This game came out one week after i finished the original VN, i was guite lucky and still completely hooked on the story. I didn't really know what to expect, after all, i knew the ending of it from the very beginning. So it came out, around 1 AM here where i live. I was too excited to sleep, so i pulled an all-nighter and played the first 11 hours until morning. And this game was quite a ride. It introduced new characters like Maho Hiyajo and Alexis Leskinen, who were quite  . But it also goes deeper into already existing characters, especially Daru, Mayuri and Rintaro, of course. And basically, the whole WWIII and Kagari story, i did not even care about it that much, i knew how it would end. It had it's twists and i did like it, but that is not what makes this VN so good.  For me it's how it treats the character of Rintaro, how it is picturing his suffering. And when the story starts moving and he \"comes back\" and finds his strenght later on, it's one of the most emotional things i have seen in any game, for me, that is. Daru through his relationship with Suzuha, and Mayuri showing how she is affected by Rintaro basically not telling her anything, ever since the beginning of the first VN, made me so much more attached to them. Overall i loved what it did, every second of it, even the comedic moments worked in this overall depressive experience. When a story surprises me and makes me cry, even though the ending is known, i know it did something right. My only real problems with this game were some characters. Not that i don't like them, the opposite, actually.  Yuki, Kagari, Kaede and Fubuki. -Kagari felt like nothing but plot device, i really really didn't feel attached to her in any way, which is sad. -Yuki. I do like her, she just lacked screentime and was also just kind of there for the plot. -Kaede. Who..? -Fubuki. NOW THIS. THIS IS PERSONAL. The whole first game, Mayuri kept mentioning her. \"Who is she?\", \"Where is she?\". That's what i asked myself.  . And you know what? I love her. She was awesome, my waiting was not for nothing. BUT SCREENTIME. She was kinda important in the Reading Steiner plot, but that simply wasn't enough for me. She deserved so much more... First of all: I love Kurisu, but actually, her being absent for most of the game, was less of a problem than i thought it would be. It completely worked without her, although i did miss her. And no, i do not prefer this over the first game. But i also do not prefer the first one over this. The experience is simply too different, but in the end i see it as one. I love it just as much, in it's own ways.  I hope you will/did enjoy it just as much as i did. 11/10 Yasuhiro Hagakure also isn't in this game, but i will let it pass again. And the +1 is because of Fubuki.", "appid": "825630", "steamid": "profiles/76561198168804685", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1538222400.0}
