{"text": "I am not very good at this game. In fact, when I played it on Switch last year, I got stuck on the Watcher Knights and put it down. But now, after a year or so, I decided I needed to finish it. I was finally able to do it this time by exploring the world more thoroughly and maintaining my momentum through the game before getting to the place where I hit a roadblock last time around. This time, I took out the Watcher Knights in three or four tries - and, damn, I felt good doing it. That's not to say that I had a wholly easier time during this playthrough - I had a lot of trouble with the Hive Knight and the final boss. I haven't even been able to finish the   final boss yet. But I had a blast swearing at my screen and holding myself back from hurling my controller across the room. I definitely intend to come back to this one (that other last boss still needs beaten and there's the additional content I haven't even touched yet), so I have no reservations about recommending it. If you haven't played it yet and enjoy challenging gameplay, definitely give it a go!", "appid": "367520", "steamid": "profiles/76561198128385623", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584100800.0}
