{"text": "\"Welcome to the machine-filled creative paradise of Scrap Mechanic, a multiplayer sandbox game with imagination and ingenuity at its core. Create fantastic machines, transforming vehicles or sneaky traps. The possibilities are endless with Scrap Mechanics powerful tools.\" Unfortunately, the games own engine can't handle all those 'powerful tools'.  Make anything with more than a few bearings or pistons on it (pretty much the core gameplay), and the frame rate will plummet. This is the worst issue you can have in a sandbox creation game, and the devs haven't even acknowledged the problem after all this time. They still publish little hotfixes here and there, but have never even mentioned this crippling issue, and seem completely unwilling to tackle the glaring issue regarding their outdated, or underpowered, physics engine. It's the only issue I, and all of my friends, have with this game. Unfortunately, the issue is fundamentally the game itself. Because of that, I can't possibly recommend this game to anyone.", "appid": "387990", "steamid": "profiles/76561198054916478", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1549108800.0}
