{"text": "I said Not Recommend, but this game has quite a bit of potential. On first experience, the mechanics are there to make this a good game. However, the game feels extremely clunky and tacky. Especially the movement. Getting stuck on objects that you really shouldn't has been a massive problem for me. The gun sway, while I respect what they're trying to do, quite a lot of the time, makes the gun play feel disgusting, and sometimes makes it downright unplayable. Leaning mechanic is also quite tacky. The map design makes it so that, a lot of the time, you'll get shot from a lot of angles, with no idea where the players have come from, only to find out that they're camping. The gameplay, I feel, relies a lot on camping. From short time playing this game, I can say that you'll encounter A ♥♥♥♥ TON of annoying, tacky gameplay mechanics that feel extremely unfinished. But hey, this is an Early Access game, so I expect that the tacky gameplay will be fixed up in the future. But right now, if you're like me, you probably wont have an enjoyable time playing this game.", "appid": "1241100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198110564469", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1587643200.0}
