{"text": "started out as interesting game. The concept and story, while cliche and dated, is presented differently, the acting is decent from most of the actors, and while you’re basically a passive participant, the story changes depending on what camera you choose to watch, and at which point. And while that is all well and good, there are a few issues, and one major one. Firstly, there is no real method of telling which timeline you’re on. There is a bar that continuously scrolls as the episodes progress, and a vertical bar shows up when you’ve crossed a scene that has altered the story. If you’re watching Kelly instead of Kelly’s dad, for example, the vertical bar will show you where the timeline is going, but not the scene that triggered it, which could potentially make things confusing. Secondly, while the acting is decent, the writing is anything but. It’s hackneyed, cliche, and just not up to what Her Story was. It’s not overtly terrible, and it’ll never go down in the annals of terrible writing, but it’s utterly nonsensical at times. Thirdly, your only option to play the game is by streaming the episodes. You cannot download them, at all. I understand why it was released this way (see Quantum Break with its TV show segments), but to not even bother adding them as an optional download is just lazy and incompetent. Now, for the main issue, and that’s that Eko seems to have abandoned the game, and refuses to fix it. As far as I can tell, there have not been any updates to the game since it came out in March, and the store page has only one news article posted, and that’s for an interview with Sam Barlow. There have been many complaints about episodes simply refusing to connect. I’ve had this issue for episode four for two months now. Trying to do the episode a few times a week, and it never is able to load. Episodes one through three worked fine, four absolutely refuses to load, and because episode five is locked until four is completed, I can’t just skip it (and watch episode four elsewhere). Supposedly, Eko has claimed they will fix it in an update, but this has failed to materialize, and the game is still broken. People have been having issues getting other episodes to load as well, which you can see by browsing the forums, or just searching. It’s been reported that Eko has been telling people to download the Android version for free, or watch it on the web for free, instead of bothering to fix the product that people paid for. As such, it seems as if Eko has abandoned the game, and has absolutely zero interest in fixing what is a major issue. The game has been out for close to four months, and not a word has been said by Eko on Steam, their Twitter, or elsewhere.  started off fine enough, quickly devolved, and due to a hands off and screw you approach by Eko games, who have chosen to ignore fixing issues in favor of being lazy and directing people to watch it for free on their website, this game is best left avoided. If bargain bins still existed, that’s where this game would end up, and that would still be too good of a place for it.", "appid": "779420", "steamid": "profiles/76561198040987377", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "29", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1530532800.0}
