{"text": "Эту игру я приобрела уже после того, как полностью прошла, специально, чтобы написать обзор (и гайд).  Несмотря на это, ставлю палец вниз, в основном из-за цены.  Для многих, кто проходил Dark Corners of the Earth, эта часть стала полным разочарованием.  Call of Cthulhu состоит из 14 глав. На каждую из них примерно 10-30 минут, то есть проходится она за ~5 часов.  Постараюсь вкратце:  За одно прохождение вполне можно получить 90% достижений. Ужасно огорчило отсутствие коллекционных карточек. Собственно,   и   - это метки, которые полностью характеризуют данную часть Call of Cthulhu. Совсем не хоррор, совсем не атмосфера.  Для тех, кто в старую игру не играл, либо с Лавкрафтом мало знаком, возможно эта часть покажется неплохой. В любом случае, я   брать её по фул прайсу. Ждите скидок, господа.", "appid": "399810", "steamid": "profiles/76561198105519640", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "80", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1541073600.0}
{"text": "As a warhammer fan and collector so far only 3 things really pissed me off   1) dawn of war 3 2) Age of ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ 3) Vermintide Now you might ask why vermintide pissed me off so badly and why i'm giving warhammer game thumb down here listen to this story. I purchased vermintide during the sale i was curious because l4d formula is enjoyable and not many games are capable of making something original in l4d style i enjoyed Deep rock galactic and even i knew that vermintide isn't deep rock galactic i still gave it a shot after launching the game i see a custom launcher with several buttons. mods button is locked and apparently is never going to be unlocked as the developers abandoned this game it feels like early access launcher and i wouldn't mind that if this was early access game and not fully paid one not to mention you can install mods from modnexus already. You can tell that game is going to be bad when once you launch the game it throws you into a game without even allowing you to edit your settings i must admit at least in vermintide you are in the inn which looks really ugly you are like whatever and you want to change your controls so after that you want to go into some action slaughter some skaven ratmen once you click on that map you are welcomed by the most disgusting and terrible designed UI in my life everything is chaotic and you have no idea what half of these buttons on your screen do then after you wake up from that shock you will get another shock and it comes from that except for the main campaign everything else on the map is locked behind a paywall so you have only 10% of the original content pretty fun right? And there are like 8 maps which is like 2 chapters from the original left 4 dead and even that game had more chapters and they weren't locked behind a paywall so you are still hoping the game is going to be fine and these things are just minor. So when i finally got into a game i noticed one thing my controls broke for some reasons my left mouse button conflicts with arrows on my keyboard and buttons are ♥♥♥♥♥♥ and often they unbind themselves for no reason this is a serious problem and it only made me more angry eventually i got lucky and managed to workaround that problem before i got smashed with another problem game has terrible colors correction everything is barely visible and you have no idea who is who, your HUD is crap, you cant even see where are you teammates l4d 90% of all maps were in super dark places where you needed flashlight and still your teammates were outlined so you could know where they are and who is player and who is a bot not in vermintide i sometimes ended up attacking my own teammate because i couldn't recognize him during skaven mob attack which is equal to zombies wave, another issuse that pissed me off was that many enemies felt like they were copy pasted from l4d enshin assassin is hunter from l4d. catcher is smoker etc,  not it only feels like the developers couldn't be bothered to make something original but they even mock it by giving us same animations for getting attacked by assassin which looks like if someone ripped  l4d animations and ported them into vermintide. whole combat feels weird its not even satisfying enemies got weird hitboxes, most of the time you have no idea where to go etc. I could continue but i feel like i have told you enough i wouldn't recommend it to anyone even to my fellow warhammer fans if you really want to play something what's really fun play Left 4 dead or deep rock galactic avoid this mess at all cost.", "appid": "235540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198067375044", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589976000.0}
