{"text": "Empires of Creation is a 2D space shooter where you   be able to build a colony of your own, gain some resources and build yourself a humongous fleet. Here's how you play the game: 1. Download the game. 2. Finish the tutorial. 3. Uninstall the game. Seriously, this game is stated being in Beta while nothing really works (at least in Windows 10). Since this is not really a game review but more of a bug report to the developers, let me start by numbering problems I found inside the game while \"playing\" (testing if anything really works) for an hour: 1. Very incomprehensibly short tutorial that didn't really teach me anything useful about the gameplay. 2. What is it with this font size 6, make it 10 so I don't have to use my magnifying glass while playing with my right foot and left hand. 3. Control keys <> aren't working and you can't change them even if you wanted to. 4. Pressing ESC while in dialogue will freeze the dialogue on screen and getting out of the game safely becomes impossible because the ESC will stop working. 5. Closing mission tab causes ship to fire when in ship controlling mode. 6. Game crashed while generating background stars for small singleplayer map. 7. In Arena, I get constantly bumped by enemy fleet. Small little ships that are 1/4 of a size of my giant USS Enterprise are able to push my ship. Physics still apply even when in space! 8. If for some reason you don't start with the tutorial it is impossible to find any habitable planet. 9. Wasn't able to buy any ships from capital planet while had 6000 currency. If you speed up the fights fast enough this becomes a   simulator with spaceships.  PLUSSES AND MINUSES: - nothing working inside the game - can't change controls - stated \"Beta\" not working properly with Windows 10 + nice concept OVERALL RATE:", "appid": "412250", "steamid": "profiles/76561197978241342", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1456228800.0}
