{"text": "From what i saw of this game it seems to tick all the boxes of what i was looking for (Space Engineers meets 7 Days 2 Die).  But unfortunately i could not get the game to run in 16/9 fullscreen in Big picture mode without game breaking graphics tearing (not a issue with my system but seems to a be linked to running some newer graphics cards and how this game handles boarderless windows since last update). Game can be played in windowed version (but this cuts off bottom of screen which has the player stats and item bar on) As i game through my TV (couch gamer) i would not recommend this game to anyone who wishes to game 16/9 fullscreen on Big Picture Mode in this format on a moden setup. Edit: I have refunded this game as i couldn't play it, but have left reveiw as stands and hope to maybe re-buy in future (as game shows promise) and revisit this reveiw. Edit: But to be honest this games community has put me off this game for good as have had so many replies to review about game settings and system specs how it cant be true what i say as they dont have same problem and its a great game. I maybe new to steam but have over 35+ years gaming and building pc's my setup is windows 10, intel i5-8400, NVMe harddrive, geforce gtx 1080 with 16gb of DD4 ram. In big picture mode can run game in all screen formats (4/3 on so on) on ultra with no problems but when switch to 16/9 i get graphics tearing i am not the only person to have had this problem if you are looking to get this game dont take my word for it just do a quick web search first (empyion and screen tearing) And to those empyrion fans who dont have this problem or just cant stand anything bad being said about there game, feel free to rate this reveiw funny (ie bad info or untrue) as the jokes only on you :)  ps: hope the devs can resolve this (they may already have but at the time i brought this it had been over 4 or 5 months and no fix) i dont think that all this games commuity is toxic but i never got to find this out and just the feed back from this reveiw from some of the games fans is enought to put me off.", "appid": "383120", "steamid": "profiles/76561198814619608", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1525435200.0}
