{"text": "So the original review was a bit too long so here is why i say dont even bother with the game -Devs dont care about what the community wants(bug fixes and other needed game balances) -Uptiering is a useless system (they will place you with much better tanks for the sake of quickly finding a game) - Pay to win, anyone who disagrees is an idiot, you level up everything twice as fast if you buy premium and the grind is sooooooo bad that it basically forces you to get it if you want to get one nation to top tier before 500 game hours -The grind, the worst i have ever seen. I actually cannot comprehend how the devs even came up with numbers that high......like 400000 Research points for one tank ( if you have premium and have a good game you will probably get around 7000-12000) - Tank upgrades, you actually have to research your crew taking care of their vehicle, lemme explain.....One modification will say replacement of filters allows for faster engine start up times, i actually have to research my crew having the ability to do basic maintenance on a military vehicle that they were trained to use. -Spawn camping, the spawn protection is a joke and never lasts longer than 5 seconds regardless of whether you leave spawn or not allowing people to attack you in spawn. -the battle rating system needs a total rework, how am i meant to feel like im in a heavy tank when i play the tiger II when people with HEATFS, a round that was not even around in WW2, can go straight through the strongest part of my armour.  Dont get it, the devs are trash. The game is boring and there are way too many things that hold back what could have been an amazing game.", "appid": "236390", "steamid": "profiles/76561198350629504", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1544270400.0}
