{"text": "Awesome game, beautiful world, beautful design, fun and gratifying gameplay til level 56, after that expect a grind but it can be fun imo. Leveling weapons and gear can be very frustrating if you dont understand the RNG lvling system they have, be sure you research this game and what to do before going all crazy with what you are given in the beginning.The game sadly gets very stagnant quicly and loses its playablity facotr, something seems to be missing. 5,000 of my hours are from AFK fishing so i didnt really play the game that muuch because I would lose interest very quickly after getting my characters to 56 or so. Now Besides ALL the P2W items and buyable items, I will leave that alone, choose to do it if you have the earning to have fun but dont let it break your back it really isnt necessary, besides you will need 4 pets at minimum to make farming and grinding easier. Now the biggest CON and this is why i will leave this game at a negative review, even though I have logged many hours and continue to play, but until this if fixed I wont change it ^^ Servers need heavy support with GMs and they need to improve the servers themselves, constant crashes around and after updates which make it very frustrating to continue after waiting to play new content.", "appid": "582660", "steamid": "profiles/76561197991741160", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1510920000.0}
{"text": "533 hours played but doesn't recommend the game?! Are you serious? Well i'm judging it by the state of the game when i stopped playing. If you're a casual player and just want to play through the campaign with a few friends and don't care about the end game grinding and difficult challenges, then i can still recommend it. But that wasn't me, so the following content of this review is about the end game and why it benefits people to ruin the game for you. The end game is dead. Reason: The people who mod item stats and duplicate OP ones due to items being localy stored and most people run maps solo because they have one character of each usable defence class anyway which they can change between during building phase and atleast one offensive dps character to get all the rewards themselves while the difficulty is lower with less people so they don't want/need you but if they have good enough gear (often moded -.-') with additional afk local co-op characters you get all the rewards for each character. So theres no reason for people to work togheter and for people with morals it's hard to \"compete\" with stores of owners who cheat their grinding and you got to just hope that the gear you buy yourself is legit. Those are the things that drained all the fun out of the game for me and many others by the looks of the increased population problems. It was one of my favourite games before i was painfully aware of the really bad stuff though. Edit: I heard they handed over the management, updates and patches to fans of the game some time after i quit. Mayby it's not such a lawless unmoderated poopieshow anymore but i don't know. Mayby i'll give the game another chance sometime to take a look.", "appid": "65800", "steamid": "profiles/76561198057131848", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1420027200.0}
