{"text": "I went into the game with almost magical sense of wonder and excitement. I've had a blast with Punch Club and I am an overall fan of Lazy Bear Games. And it is enjoyable... For a little while. I wanted to like it, I really did! Unfortunately Swag and Sorcery plays like an idle game in which you can't properly idle - it requires your attention for very little, but   often. And I am not a stranger to idle games - I am a long time player of Crusaders of the Lost Idols. Comparing the two titles, Swag and Sorcery feels like a demo of the Crusaders... A paid demo. I have played my fair share of grindy MMORPGs, so I am not annoyed or opposed to a grind. The difference here is, that the grind doesn't feel rewarding. It is too much for too little. You repeat and repeat \"dungeons\" to collect resources to craft items, that you sell to buy upgrades that are underwhelming and mostly +1 to a stat.", "appid": "929010", "steamid": "profiles/76561198114568042", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557489600.0}
