{"text": "Serious Sam 3: BFE is a disappointing entry in the Serious Sam franchise. The Serious Sam games work for reasons this game has seem to have forgotten, having terrible new enemies and gameplay features. There are certainly fun moments (particularly near the end of the campaign) but they are largely dwarfed by some really awful decisions. PROS: - Shooting feels great and responsive - Some of the later campaign levels feel like an old Serious Sam game and present a healthy challenge - There are a great amount of settings to customize - Pretty lengthy campaign, taking around 10 hours on a first time playthrough CONS: - Some awful levels, the first half of the game takes place mostly in cramped urban areas, the opposite of what makes the past Serious Sam games great - Terrible additions to gameplay (including reloading and sprinting) that are incompatible with Serious Sam - Pretty generic and lackluster visuals, with dust frequently blinding the player to nearby enemies (something that could not have been intentional) - Annoying, dark underground sections that resemble a bad horror game - Terrible new enemies (with way too many hitscanners) and notable holes in the Serious Sam arsenal - Some shocking performance issues, even with modern hardware - Overpriced, especially for an almost decade old game", "appid": "41070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198272326993", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "20", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596369600.0}
