{"text": "I'm no stranger to idle / clicker games in any way - I enjoy the constant restart and grind, the constant format of doing your best to get faster and faster to complete. In fact, I quite enjoy them and I have a lot of fun with them, there's no pressure to have to remember to log in every day, to do this or that.  With that being said, I cannot stand this game. Idle Heist is one of the worst clicker games I have come across. With some achievements that take forever (needing 1,000 in game bomb currency whilst getting mostly 1 bomb per day via the Daily Reward), the developer has gone out their way to try and make you buy game packs from the store for a free game - whilst not inherently unseen throughout the genre, most give you an ample way to constantly make the in game currencies to progress without needing to purchase.  There's no mechanism for restart, meaning you're stuck on the constant same grind, some achievements require one million clicks - there's no way you're going to be able to complete this game without an auto clicker unless you're looking to get an RSI. The graphics always lag out for the few moments that they're on screen and there's just literally no enjoyment in this. I regret starting it, I regret thinking this would be an easy grind completion for my percentage. I cannot non-recommend this game enough.", "appid": "858060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198385501958", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584619200.0}
