{"text": "Let's say I need to start this review by saying that I LOVE visual novels. Katawa Shoujo, Cinders, , Kira Kira, Dear Drops, Hatoful Boyfriend, Quartett and others titles from this genre are something I read and enjoyed most of them as all of them contained really good stories with interesting and likeable characters (Misha hardcore fan from Katawa Shoujo :D) with that important element, which make me come back to them and read them again. They were all special in their own ways.  But unfortunately there are some Visual Novels which lack in many elements, making them unfortunately inferior to other titles of this genre. Unfortunately Sakura Spirit is one of those titles. And trust me, I'm REALLY lenient on how I review Visual Novels, as I have soft spot for them in my heart. But I can't force myself to give positive review for this one. Normally I would start by saying how plot looks like and what you may expect from the story, but problem is that... story here doesn't really exist. I realize what kind of genre this VN hits into (I LOVE Ecchi, so yeah :D), but you know, I expect something else as a bonus to at least review it in positive way. To summarize it it's about a hero which is promising Kung-Fu fighter which ends up in another world after visiting certain temple to pray for some luck. Later it's just 2 fights, some dialogues which don't really add anything useful to the story and mostly embarrasing situations which are the essence of ecchi stories (yeah, BOOBIES) and... that's it. In this VN there is ONE route and TWO choices where you 'decide' what happens next and those choices make story look really similar to each other. When you compare it to something like Kira Kira which may last even +40 hours or more, this is just depressing. Sorry folks, Visual Novels are about reading story and it's hard to call this a story when it's so short. It should take you max 3 hours if you are really lenient and 1,5-2 hours if you read it at somewhat decent pace. Also I noticed lots of grammatical issues, which let's face it shouldn't really happen in something that is all about reading (and enjoying some views :D). For me at this point this title looks like an incomplete VN with just one route and... zero additional content, in almost hardcore alpha state, which shouldn't be released yet in my opinion. But I need to say that one thing in this title is good - Art. Girls are sexy, adorable and well, you may enjoy their looks for sure. If you look for eye candy when it goes to art, this one is pretty good choice in this regard. I need to salute and congratulate the artist, as he did one hell of a work. I can't say bad word about it. To summarize it - it's ecchi title which is just... ecchi. It provides nothing else as story pretty much doesn't exist and it's so short that 10 euro is too high of a price tag for a title with flaws glaring as those. While I love to look at some anime-like ladies and I'm big fan of ecchi, I'm afraid good art alone isn't even close to give this title a serious consideration. Buy it ONLY on serious discount and if you are hardcore ecchi fan. My honest advice.", "appid": "313740", "steamid": "profiles/76561198060771114", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1410091200.0}
