{"text": "If you are a Star Wars fan and looking for some new and engaging Star Wars stories, then this is the game for you. Star Wars the Old Republic is full of phenomenal class campaigns, with eight in total and hours of playtime in store for each of them however it unfortunately fails as an MMORPG. If you are not a Star Wars fan and are instead looking for a new MMORPG to invest yourself in, then I can't recommend this game. SWTOR is best described as an mmoRPG, with a major emphasis on the RPG while the MMO elements are lacking. The reason this game failed after launch and died was due to it being herald as the WoW Killer which of course, it never lived up to as the PvE and PvP elements of the game were lackluster and the end game was pretty bad. I do highly regret pre-purchasing the Collector's Edition of this game but I at least found some fun in leveling my first few characters. As for the expansions, I've heard they've gotten better overtime but I have only played the first one, which was total ♥♥♥♥. The game has also aged pretty badly, especially in the graphics department but the story is still great and worthwhile. I just hope that this game's failure discourages future Star Wars MMORPGs as this game had a LOT of potential. In conclusion, SWTOR is a great RPG but fails in many MMO aspects however is still worth playing if you are a Star Wars fan.", "appid": "1286830", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084468190", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1595937600.0}
