{"text": "PlayerUnknown's Unoptimized Garbage But seriously, this game   fun. I remember when Fortnite performed as bad as this game. Now Fortnite is leagues better and the connection and hitreg is extremely consistent. This game keeps getting worse and worse as the updates come. I have an i7 5820K, R9 390, and 16GB of RAM. While my GPU isn't that high end anymore, it should be more than sufficient to push a game with such terrible (read: terrible) visuals to 144fps on low settings. However, it consistently hangs anywhere in between 70 and 140, usually closer to 70 than 140. It's disgusting and it keeps getting worse as the updates come. Meanwhile Fortnite just keeps getting better. This game keeps getting worse and it shows as the player count keeps dropping. They are now pushing out a third map, which runs like garbage in comparison to the first and second map on the test servers. I got 30 fps in one of the map locations. 30!!!! My graphics drivers are updated. I don't have performance dips like this on the other maps (they still run terribly anyway on lowest settings) and none of my other games have problems.  They are already teasing a fourth map that comes out this winter. They are making boatloads of money yet they can't hire any competent developers. Their community managers on Reddit make it out to be some extremely hard task in finding competent people to program for their game, which it clearly is not as Fortnite started out with a small team and it's still expanding and quality has only improved as time goes on.  They added map selection in April, a very long awaited feature. They are now removing it because they are afraid it will divide the playerbase too much between the first two maps. I've got something to say Blueballs: if your second map ran better and was generally positively recieved (news flash: it isn't), maybe people would play it more. Stop fixing issues with bandaids and do the surgery required. It's sad because if this game ran and played well I would play it more than Fortnite because I prefer FPP and weapon recoil over bloom. But this game fails to deliver, time and time again. Fortunately I was never afflicted by the random ban waves but the second that does happen, I am done with this game for good.", "appid": "578080", "steamid": "profiles/76561198054276000", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1529496000.0}
