{"text": "Something must've gone really wrong during the development of this game. I have no idea how so many people ended up giving it positive reviews, but there are many things that are just unexplainably   about it. Long story short, this game lacks \"juice\", a game design term that refers to things such as SFX, movements of stuff on screen, screenshake, things that make you   the game, basically. Now, for a more detailed explanation/enumeration: Now the absolutely worst thing of all, what for me, takes this game from \"bad\" to \"uncomprehensible\", is the art. Generally, when a game is bad, it is all bad, at least when it's an indie game. But in this game, the art is absolutely gorgeous. But why was it put into this game? Why does it seem like the developer just dropped the PNGs into Unity, made them move around a bit, and called it a day? It just doesn't fit. That being said, the animation of the big circle rotating in the main menu is nice; that's about it though, one of the few things the art was put to good use for. I assume either the dev and artist are different people, and the dev comissioned the art for boatloads of money (or the artist was the dev's friend and made it all for free, or they worked as a team, in which case I would say the artist did a hell of a lot more work than the dev), or they are the same person, and while this person was extremely good at art, they just didn't have sufficient experience and/or knowledge about game design and development to properly make the game. Now for some more personal gripes, which might just be attributed to me being stupid: Not going to make any particular comments about the gameplay, because it's just sort of bland, as you'd expect. Basically, if you like well made shmups with sounds and effects that all mesh together perfectly, and   gameplay,  don't buy this. If you just like looking at pretty pictures, buy it I guess, though you could also do that from YouTube.", "appid": "720150", "steamid": "profiles