{"text": "There are many things that are wrong with this game, i think it's better for me to list them off. Minuses 1.Character's vocabulary is built by profanities and many different ways of saying the Lord's name 2.Character can't shut up for a minute or less, ruining the immersion, the thing that is said to be the meta of this game 3.The monster encounters went from scary to frustrating 4.The game doesn't strike with much immersion, as i have referanced in the previous point 5.The game is BUILT by accidents, literally every ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ second you see an entryway, an escape a sanctuary a route the game always has to snatch it away from you to extend your play time. 6.Jumpscares... 7.The monsters have slightly downgraded in design, you have 2 skinwalker like creatures and a single interesting one. The older Amnesia games have had a backstory or meaning of the creatures design, either that or they were really unique, Take the suitor for example: A tortured man who has fallen  was once the main antagonist's lover, yet it he has fallen for a trap leading him down a path of torture. He has a wheel on his neck so he can't sleep, he has cuts on his chest which might indicate slashings, chains all around his body which reduced him from moving. The gatherer and the brute were Alexanders servants possibly contorted and mangled by the guardian, the brute's body was possibly put together with metal scraps and his split open face was forgotten, the gatherer was probably treated the same as the brute, covered with strips of leather to merge his body together. The Creatures from AMFP were hybrids of a man and a pig, failed experiments and had an interesting look to themselves. This doesn't really happen in the newest addition. 8. The themes of the monsters in earlier games had an accent, a tone to them, the music in The dark descent was memorable and unique but the music in rebirth was rather forgetable Plusses 1.Very good graphics 2.Reintroduction of old locations like brennenburg made the game alot more interesting and fun, yet the devs didn't expand it to it's peak", "appid": "999220", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996088133", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603454400.0}
