{"text": "Maplestory 2 is a Korean MMO, with everything that entails. It is extremly grindy, which can be an issue for some but not necessarily a bad thing. The classes are fun enough and varied enough to be engaging. Combat is very simplistic and at least on some classes it encourages just choosing the skills you want spammed via the inbuilt macro buttons. The autoaim is a mess and manual aim with a mouse is not an option.  The game has a lot of different things to do, but its all menial work. They have lifeskills, including manually farming, forging, etc but it includes spamming F while standing in one place for a while, then moving onto the next thing, and then the next. Its so boring, that they sell a badge in their marketplace for AU$5 a  month that spams the F key for you. Everything seems to be time gated. You can only do x amount of dungeons a week, x amount of forging, farming, etc.  The game itself is not that bad, and can be fun. However there is a lot of RNG involved. To unlock your accessory to all 3 slots,  firstly you need fragments by doing dungeons. Then spend 500k on each accessory, which is a lot in this game to make it into an accessory. Then the accessory has to be a good RNG roll on attributes. Then those rolls have to be a high value to be of use. If you try to use accessory reroll scrolls, which cost about 5.5mil currently to even have a chance at getting one, you are more likely to get a worse roll. Then there are slots. Each accessory needs other similar accessories for a chance to slot them and in the process destroying the other. Of course, these slots fail very often, which can be quite expensive.  Basically, the game isnt bad, but the amount of busywork and RNG/Timegated stuff just makes it not rewarding. I played it for a few days and realized that I was just logging on, doing my dailies, trying to slot my accessories, etc and constantly failing and generally just not feeling like I was progressing or any sense of reward. Games that make you play need to make you feel that you are getting rewarding for investing your time in the game, not that you are struggling to progress despite the time you are sinking in the game.  Then there are the scummy practices of the devs. Based on tests done with attribute scrolls, about 5% or less will get a decent RNG rolls, while most people get useless rolls. Devs have officially denied there is a weight to RNG, but community testing has shown that is a lie. It is the same for gemstone upgrade chances. Officially it specifies a success rate but its actually a lot less than what it says based on what the community testing has shown. The devs of the game can simply not be trusted. That said, they do listen to the community and make changes in response. Just not always the changes that would be helpful.  This game was P2W in Korea, but the international version has those P2W elements stripped. However they didnt replace the P2W stuff with ingame stuff that can be earned. So now the game is in a weird place where its just too slow to progress without the P2W items which dont exist.  There is a lot more I can talk about for example the gemstone system, where you can only buy a certain amount of material needed to upgrade them a week, where they lie about the upgrade rate, etc, but the short of it is that this a game that will suck up your time. If you have excess time, feel free to give it a try, but dont expect it to be a rewarding experience. I am sure there are people who enjoy this sort of thing, but unfortunately its not for me. I like grindy games as long as they can make the experience feel rewarding, and this game certainly fails at that.", "appid": "560380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198018554040", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1545307200.0}
