{"text": "the basic idea is awesome. mine stuff, build stuff, farm stuff, kill stuff. classic minecraft experience but in a serie of mini maps instead of big open world. Character customisation (lacking but still present), classes (wich is rare in this type of game), pets. But i cannot recommend this game because the devs seem to focus more on adding new elements to the already broken game rather than fixing what needs to be. Best exemple i can give is: playing ranged class is impossible as the crossair keeps going left or right of the screen every now and then. you put your crossair in middle of the screen to shoot an ennemy and see your fireball shooting 2-4 inches on the right of where youre aiming.... Devs are giving a workaround but it keep breakin again and again so every 5 minutes you need to pause and change your resolution 3 or 4 times until its fixed again.... that is a big game-breaker for me.  Also the sync between players is horrible, even with amazing internet connection, i keep seeing my wife where she is not and when she holds a torch, it lights the room for her but leaves me in the dark. In first person, your weapon completely block your view, pets are an annoyance as theyre also always blocking your view. mining is a pain as you aim at a block to mine it but end up mining the block next to it because of the crossair bug. building is equally a pain for the same reason, aim to place a block and end up placing it next to where you wanted. So short story, if the crossair and torch problems were solved i would totally recommend this game, but as it is, it feels like the game should still be in early access.... I dont see how it can be considered fully functional and i do not recommend it.", "appid": "374040", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041779541", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1493899200.0}
