{"text": "I remember a day I was playing football with my friends when I was a kid. Older kids came, took our ball, kicked us off the field. That was a sad day. Than, I remember a girl - I had a big crush on her. She friendzoned me completely, I was listening to bulls**t like what she want her perfect boyfriend to be like, etc., for many, many weeks. That were sad months. Than, I remember my dog was sick. I had to take him to the vet. He told me he's in bad shape. I had to put him down. That was one of the worst days of my life. Than, I bought Omerta. Now, seriously. I've played Omerta year earlier, for like 50hrs. I must say it was waaay better than, but I see some improvements too. Still, I can't imagine how anyone can take so awesome idea and make the game so bad. It seems like the entire crew tried to make something great and than there would appear this guy - messing up the code, f***ing with gameplay and inserting bugs & glitches. They don't update it anymore, so: F*CK YOU, GAMERS! WE ALREADY GOT YOUR MONEY, SO YOU CAN S*CK OUR D. Few most annoying things: * Cover system is f**ked up - you can hide behind a solid, marble pillar, covering my whole character, but a guy with f**cking Thompson is accurately firing him from like 50m. * But when I try to hit guy covered behind a bush, he can't hit him with a rifle from 40m (!). F**K LOGIC! * Messages saying mission was \"successful\", but nothing happens. * Random fight, my chars start in the f**king middle of an open field, enemy is starting first, killing 3 of 4 my guys. WELL PLAYED! Seriously, I got this game only because it was in the bundle and I still wonder if I would buy it again. This game is so frustrating because it looks great, at the beginning you enjoy it a lot, than you starting to see how f**ked it is. NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE NOPE N