{"text": "Overall - Complicated Review here Score: 7/10 Game will challenge your thinking about the FPS genre a bit and force you to make decisions that may come during realistic situations as perhaps depicted in the game. The voice acting, sound, etc, is pretty good. The game is immersive. Sometimes you fight the controls. The story will keep you going even if the game play starts to peter out. Game has won awards... All that being said, I wouldn't recommend it. Normally I recommend everything over a score of 5. I did not like the game. Below if you want reasons. Game has been bundled, I would never pay full price. Story: The story is interesting and unique and pits the player in an interesting situation where they are under the assumption that they will be helping in a crisis area. Characters are believable and you can relate to them. However, I didn't actually enjoy the story. Gameplay: Realistic type FPS. Personally that's a no go for me typically. If you like that type of FPS, then this game is probably a bit more for you, however the controls will still leave you wanting. Harder difficulties may end up with enemies being bullet sponges. Cause that's fun.  Audio: Overall, this was definitely my favorite part. I enjoyed the voice acting and the music. It was always appropriate to what the developers were trying to convey during the story. Graphics: Game is a bit dated, but still the graphics were good for this style of game. They'd probably be a bit better if I had a better card, but with what I had, I was content.  Final Notes: While the game was innovative and definitely an experience, I didn't really enjoy it and therefore wouldn't recommend it even though technically it hits all the marks to be recommended. I went into it not knowing anything about the game, and came out understanding why it was a commercial failure but still received(was nominated for?) awards.  If you're looking for something different, and don't have my issues as listed above, then get the game and give it a go, but if you are looking for a good time, and to enjoy a story and not deal with cognitive dissonance, take a pass.", "appid": "50300", "steamid": "profiles/76561197985759517", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1477051200.0}
