{"text": "I beat this game in one sitting. I referenced a guide one time for a puzzle I was unable to complete. Abandoned is a very short, point n' click, escape the room style puzzle game. When I say short I mean for most people it'll take an hour tops. There's a simple plot about looking for your missing brother which, spoiler alert, has nothing to spoil. The story is hardly brought up and has little relevancy to anything you do or see. Basically he found another dimension and you are following his trail to try and find him. The puzzles are simple and mostly what you'd expect from one of these games. None of them gave me any trouble save for one. It is probably the hardest puzzle in the game and its a shame that I was challenged for all the wrong reasons. There's a cube made up of 8 rooms where you can change the color of each. Outside of the cube is a rotating hologram of the cube with the color combination you need for each section of the cube. The problem is, the hologram is rotating and flickering at the same time. The 'puzzle' here is you have to figure out which room is the room you enter from so that you know where the other colors go in relation. This isn't too hard but the big issue with this puzzle is this: I'm colorblind. Not to the degree that some people are but just enough that it makes it hard to differentiate between similar colors, like the four shades of blue in this puzzle. It wouldn't even be that bad if it wasn't for the flickering and rotating. I realize that this won't affect everyone but it did annoy me. Without that issue I'm sure the puzzle's pretty easy actually. Beyond that every puzzle was straight forward. Too easy in fact which made me feel like I was wasting my time. And there's no real reward for solving the puzzles. You aren't really given any substantial info about why the world you're in works the way it does or why lightbulbs are so damned important. The art is actually quite good but it does nothing to tell you about this alien world, its importance, history or why the hell you should care about it other than your brother was there at some point. This game could take place in a normal city setting and it would work just as well in terms of story. So the puzzles are easy and the story is pointless. I just don't see what you are meant to get out of this game. If one was decent than it could justify the other's shortcomings. But as it is, apart from the art it has very little to offer and is less appealing than most of the free games of similar style on newgrounds.  Summary: +Art ~Very short -Easy Puzzles -Anti Color-Blind Puzzle -Bland and Pointless story I have heard good things about the sequel so maybe the developer learned from this first one.", "appid": "389270", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041006664", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1487937600.0}
