{"text": "*sigh* this is the most bipolar game ive ever played period  i love and hate this game  pros: -Japanese history and mythology and story is well executed for the fantasy game its trying to be imo.   -fun ninja and mage buffs and skills -your character looks cool af with well made sword and armor models  -good arrow and gun system (though a little slow) -stances and ki system  -   and welcome to another episode of devs dont know wt♥ they made: -this game shouldent (have a/focus on) pvp, for better gameplay balance insted -this game shouldent restrict coop before finishing a level to punish veteran players (lol?) -levelling in this game is more like necessity to get 2 shotted instead of getting one shotted -allow me to parry yokai  -allow me to parry reverse enemy projectile coz itd look cool  -allow me to punish out of key yokai and bosses with good looking attack and actual damage instead of 0 poise for some hits  -add stagger/stagger buildup to weapons  (my odachi high stance dosent stagger but dual katana dude staggers me lol) -the game should allow you to grind the skill and materials to craft/upgrade weapons and armors rarely dropped from enemies using crafting materials commonly-uncommonly dropped by certain enemies -skills should be complimentary to get cool op ish or gimmicky builds not nessecity -MAKE SLOTH TALISMAN ONLY AVAILABLE TO HIGH OMNYO BUILDS  -MAKE SLOTH TALISMAN SPEED -20% INSTEAD OF WHAT SEEMS -50% -stop going insane with \"its hard so its good philosophy\". no i wont get good. -(optional)dont make every boss terra from kh ? (and on top of that 2 at once!)  TLDR:this game feels like it wants to be some God Eater/monster hunter esc game with ninja gaiden mechanics and souls level design but it end up feeling like random mix of disgaea ,diablo ,souls and candy crush with a good enough story. i recommend and dont recommend this game i cant give a mid review on steam but ginchiyo, okatsu and fuku are good enough reason for positive review alone.   Edit : and maria. Edit2: i was enjoying ng+ got some good gear and rekt two of 2v1 fights. it felt good and i enjoyed thoroughly it but then i went in dlc area to fight date masamune and why the heck is dlc area in so over leveled no area gives that much amrita to level up unless i grind ng quests   now i hate this game  this games reward for trying and learning is to level cap forcing player into grinding  not to mention there are like 8 type of enemies constantly being reused through majority of game. dlc has new enemies but thats also overcapped.    idk what they were thinking while designing it this way and despite my tries to like this game, this game keeps pulling stupid design decisions  some people may highly enjoy this game   but for me its a really bad game with bad game design only worth for it story, chars and world building. its sad to me because i really liked this game in concept but it constantly fails in execution constantly in exchange to be more hard.i cant recommend this to anyone anymore because it has too much artificial difficulty in it.  buy sekiro instead", "appid": "485510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198089763092", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597492800.0}
