{"text": "EDIT: BUY THE HD COLLECTION INSTEAD! THE ISSUES ARE FIXED THERE! I have played DMC 3 everywhere that it is possible, from the PS2 to PC, it always stays the same, and awesome and incredible game, that surpasses the reboot in story and characters, and clashes in gameplay with it, if you're one of these people with an OCD to perfect things, boy, You'll suffer here. And love it. This is a great hack'n'slash game and all, I love this series alot and I'm a great fan, but this PC port is completely borked. Depending on hardware, it can either have horrible performance issues, or not even start at all, no matter what you do, so I don't recommend buying this until Capcom lifts their asses and come fix and promote again this great game. The only way you can run the game without modding it is probably having the supported specs. Because anything else is impossible. Yeah I know, you can mod it to fix stuff and add style switching, and delete sounds files to fix performance, but that's stuff fans/users have to do. The game shouldn't be ready and broken to the consumer like this. I'd consider rebuying it if the price remained the same and problems were fixed. Bad Capcom.", "appid": "6550", "steamid": "profiles/76561198085772203", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "42", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1509537600.0}
