{"text": "This one was hard for me. I actually did like the Arctic Cruise part quite a bit (although I can't stand when the seals talk, seriously WHY). I did think it was way too short though. The actual design of the levels is quite lovely. There's a seal that says \"egg\". Overall, I don't really have a problem with Arctic Cruise besides it being short. But then there's Death Wish. There's some enjoyable challenges here, but then there's quite a few that are just awful because of the way that they try to challenge you -- it's just not a good way of doing it and in order to 100% the game, you HAVE to finish the death wishes. IMO this would've been a far better idea for a new game+ or master mode or whatever that overall increases the difficulty of the base game to be harder instead of doing this challenge mode where you have to finish levels in a certain amount of jumps or ones where you can't even jump at all... or boss rush where if you move onto a boss with 1 out of 4 health left, if you die then you respawn with ONE OUT OF FOUR HEALTH AND YOU ONLY HAVE THREE LIVES TOTAL. Ugh. I will admit that I do really love the time rift collapses of Death Wish. The music's awesome and the levels look really neat with a sense of \"everything's falling apart\". Unfortunately though I think I'm going to have to not recommend this DLC. A Hat in Time set the bar very high in terms for what DLC for the game should meet or exceed, but with Arctic Cruise being too short and Death Wish being painful in one of the worst ways it can be, this DLC does not meet that bar.", "appid": "787340", "steamid": "profiles/76561197990323026", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "17", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1559563200.0}
{"text": "*Controles confusos. *Uma quantidade de bugs absurda (Passar 30 minutos tentando matar um boss e quando o hp dele está pela metade cair  cenário adentro sem uma forma aparente de sair e observar o boss se regenerando, perdendo todo seu progresso não é exatamente o que eu chamo de diversão. Mesmo que você consiga \"unstuckar\" usando o mapa do jogo [Coisa que eu só descobri gastando um bom tempo no google procurando por uma solução que não fosse criar um novo personagem].   *O preço absurdo dos reparos de itens. Ou você conserta o item ou anda nu esperando juntar almas o suficiente para comprar alguma coisa decente. *Ainda não entendi direito a ideia de Ascender. Ao longo do jogo você recebe várias vezes uma mensagem dizendo que você já pode Ascender, mas nenhuma explicação plausível é oferecida. O que você sabe é que o char morre. Ponto. Não fica claro se você será obrigado a escolher um novo deus para seguir, se algum equipamento fica com você, se ascender faz você voltar ao começo do jogo... Enfim. *O ser humano que conseguir matar The Beast F'taga na faca, por favor me mande uma msg.", "appid": "233630", "steamid": "profiles/76561198097123331", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1404907200.0}
{"text": "这游戏就离谱。说好了让亚罗伊当追寻者——“想去哪儿就去哪儿”——结果前脚离开圣地后脚就把主角锁外面了，想回去拿动力电池都困难重重。这就好比招工的时候说好包吃包住五险一金，结果把人骗来了没吃没住没险没金，你们这是部落还是黑煤矿啊，你们这个部落害人不浅啊。 但是这不是最离谱的，最离谱的是，大门锁了，守卫誓死不让主角通过——但是这游戏竟然能 通 过 爬 山 翻 进 圣 地！这漏洞就离谱。既然你建模都包不住圣地，又何苦把大门锁上呢。如实兑现追寻者的待遇承诺不好吗。然而，如果说这个漏洞离谱，接下来的部分简直就是令人生草。 开发商为了不让玩家爬山，没有选择用建模把圣地包住——而是立了两堵硕大的空气墙。没错，空气墙！两堵！但是令人生草的是，这两堵空气墙，第一堵墙能挡人，但是挡不住马…挡不住马……挡不住马………人骑着马就穿过去了啊喂(wºДº)w！而第二堵墙，是漏的…是漏的……是漏的………玩家可以从某个地方翻滚穿过去，完全没有起到空气墙的效果……所以你为什么要立这两堵空气墙啊(wºДº)w！建模给我认真一点啊(wºДº)w！把大门给我打开啊(wºДº)w！ 2017年的游戏，到2020年完全版了还有这种神秘bug实在是令人生草，游骑兵你可长点心吧(눈_눈)。 评价：A - 这绝对不是一款烂游戏，但是有很严重的缺陷，所以也称不上是款好游戏。可以玩，但是没必要。It's not bad, but deeply flawed, so it's not good either. You can play if you want, but you are not missing anything if you don't.", "appid": "1151640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198081149130", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "21", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596888000.0}
